Rupert was a guest on the Chairman’s Conversation, an annual event hosted by the radio station’s founder, Given Mkhari. He was accused of being arrogant, racist and suffering from cognitive dissonance during the interview, which was also broadcast on eNCA. During the interview, Rupert – who is chair of the Swiss-based, luxury-goods company Richemont, as well as of South African-based company Remgro – touched on various topics, including corruption, land expropriation, investor confidence, building a sustainable business, and the Afrikaner Broederbond during a two-hour interview. 